<br>
I performed a test.  I summoned a pet and suspended it, that worked fine.  Then, I let my pet hit the other group's mob once, and then I had it back off until the other group's mob was dead.  Sure enough, I wasn't able to suspend my pet, because &quot;my pet is the focus of something's attention.&quot;<br>
<br>
I zoned over to Maiden's Eye to perform the same test, had no problems at all.<br>
<br>
Anybody have a similiar problem? <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168753"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.pacbell.net/ping000/Rasc-sig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yamp>Yamp</A> at: 11/10/02 10:25:39 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ommundan>Ommundan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.datecc.de/bilder/woag/bilder/misc/misc59d.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of The Hunt</span><br>  Posts: 281<br> <font color=#333333>(11/10/02 10:43:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=435.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.cfl.rr.com/exarch/files/PAINT1.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Suspended Minion - a problem?</span><hr size=1> Maybe some weird example of zonewide agro? Could be certain mobs are &quot;aware&quot; of you killing their friends?<br>
<br>
I seem to remember a long long time ago having a problem where on kind of mob or NPC would not usually hate me UNLESS I killed one of their buddies and then even if it was across the zone when I can within range they would attack.<br>
<br>
I remember that it wasn't faction based.<br>
<br>
I &quot;think&quot; it may have been with my druid versus animals. After killing them she would loose that &quot;animals like me&quot; quality for a while. I can't say for sure because I never did detailed checks.<br>
<br>
I've read some very good posts here and there about how agro works and how calls for help leave a flag on a character (or in this case your pet I guess) that modifies agro range on mobs. This is why pullers will often camp out even when they know feign death has worked. Monkly Buisness has (maybe had, I haven't been there in a LONG time) some very good threads on this stuff.<br>
<br>
Some things to test out...<br>
<br>
1. Try an air pet and see if it's invis helps.<br>
<br>
2. Make sure you've /pet back off'd bobber before trying SA.<br>
<br>
3. Make a note of what type of mobs this happens with.<br>
 3a. Is it all mobs?<br>
 3b. Is it one specific type of mob. (Maybe the aliens are hive minded?)<br>
<br>
4. I would definetly be interested in seeing if this happens in other zones.<br>
<br>
If you can repeat this every time, definetly /bug it. I would also suggest everyone else with this skill test it and /bug it also.<br>
<br>
Good luck,<br>
<br>
